    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b2eb74db_8067df2b",
        "filename": "common/flag/commalist.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-27T00:49:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To summarize our discussion, let me list pros/cons of each approach to the best of my understanding:\n\n1) as is in this patchset:\n + allows evolution of impl, w/o interfaces changes, hence cheaper.\n - more complex interface\n\n2) using int64slice design:\n - can\u0027t evolve much w/o interface changes, hence evolution is costlier.\n + easier interface, easier implementation\n\nPlease, correct me if I am wrong.\n\nAnd if you agree with above, then I posit that 2) beats 1) because evolution is unlikely, and even if evolution must be done, backwards incompatible changes have been done to **code** in this repo, it\u0027s not an insurmountable problem because:\n * it\u0027s Go, so one can use gorename and friends, compiler makes such changes less costly and less risky (vs Python)\n * we pin all luci-go repo usages and recommend others to do the same (see README.md of this repo)), hence propagating refactoring is also straightforward (but, yes, will take more CLs)\n\nHave I convinced you? :)",
      "parentUuid": "8b73ef46_118fb62d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 26,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "d9df298682cc8dc9254f67a2255f1cc90c6a11c9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7dfc4317_097ed389",
        "filename": "common/flag/commalist.go",
